## Test Case 7: Access Profile Without Token

**Request:**
```http
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
```

**Expected Response (401):**
```json
{
  "message": "Access denied. No token provided."
}
```

**Status:** ⬜ Pass / ⬜ Fail

---

## Test Case 8: Access Profile With Valid Token

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_FROM_TEST_4
```

**Request:**
```http
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
```

**Expected Response (200):**
```json
{
  "advocate": {
    "id": 2,
    "name": "Test Advocate",
    "email": "test@law.com",
    "phone": "9876543210",
    "created_at": "2026-03-07T..."
  }
}
```

**Status:** ⬜ Pass / ⬜ Fail

---

## Test Case 9: Access Profile With Invalid Token

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here
```

**Request:**
```http
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
```

**Expected Response (403):**
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid token"
}
```

**Status:** ⬜ Pass / ⬜ Fail

---

## Test Case 10: Login with Missing Fields

**Request:**
```http
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@law.com"
}
```

**Expected Response (400):**
```json
{
  "message": "Email and password are required"
}
```

**Status:** ⬜ Pass / ⬜ Fail

---

## Manual Testing Checklist

After completing all tests:

- [ ] Registration works with valid data
- [ ] Registration rejects duplicate emails
- [ ] Registration validates required fields
- [ ] Login works with valid credentials
- [ ] Login rejects invalid credentials
- [ ] Login validates required fields
- [ ] Profile route requires authentication
- [ ] Profile returns user data with valid token
- [ ] Profile rejects invalid tokens
- [ ] Password is NOT returned in any response
- [ ] Token contains user ID and email

---

## Automated Testing (Optional)

You can use tools like:
- **Postman**: Import this file as collection
- **Thunder Client**: VS Code extension
- **Insomnia**: REST API client
- **curl**: Command line tool

Example curl command:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"Test User","email":"test@example.com","password":"123456","phone":"1234567890"}'
```

